    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR2a0001-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:45:02.003+09:00">As for Han Fei</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:46:02.504+09:00">he was one of the princes of Han.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:51:58.333+09:00">He took pleasure in the study of 'titles and performance' and 'the arts of the rule of law',</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:53:12.085+09:00">but his ultimate basic concern was with the the Huang-Lao (Daoism).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:53:48.605+09:00">As a matter of personal detail, Fei had a stutter</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2023-03-16T06:03:49.67+09:00">and was incapable of speaking in public</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2023-03-16T06:04:56.045+09:00">and so he excelled at the composition of texts.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:55:21.155+09:00">Together with Li Si he studied under Xun Qing,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-13a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:56:08.494+09:00">and there Si had an inferiority complex vis-a-vis Fei.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:56:58.573+09:00">When Fei realised that (his state of) Han was being decimated and weakened</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:57:33.423+09:00">he repeatedly remonstrated with the King of Han through letters.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T17:58:19.255+09:00">The King of Han (however) was incapable of using his advice.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:27:08.884+09:00">At this point Han Fei took strong exception to the failure - in government - to make it one's main business to cultivate to transparency the system of the rule of law.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:32:31.731+09:00">(the failure to) maintain a firm grip on one's position of power in controlling ministers and subjects</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:32:41.327+09:00">to enrich the state and strengthen its armies and on that basis to seek a staff, and to employ men of talent,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:36:13.459+09:00">and instead the practice of appointing to high office frivolous vermin and of placing them in charge of men of concrete achievement and substance.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:38:31.612+09:00">He was of opinion that that Confucians confused the rule of law through there literary works,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:50:49.344+09:00">and that the roving knights used their arms to offend against prohibitions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:52:36.565+09:00">that in stressless times one should show fondness for men of a high reputation</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T18:53:13.6+09:00">and in stressed conditions one should employ armoured officers.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T19:11:03.562+09:00">In his own time what was cultivated was not practiced,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T19:12:06.504+09:00">and what was put into practice was not properly cultivated .</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T19:25:03.061+09:00">He found it tragic how moral purity and moral straightness was given no room by wicked and warped ministers.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T19:26:03.877+09:00">He contemplated on the changes of success and failure in the past,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T19:26:20.432+09:00">and then he created</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-14a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T19:27:02.706+09:00">more than a hundred thousand words in all.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:25:40.368+09:00">Someone passed on the book and it got to Qin.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:26:38.36+09:00">When the King of Qin saw the books Gufen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:26:40.462+09:00">and Five Vermin</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:26:44.094+09:00">he said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:27:15.103+09:00">"Wow!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:27:50.811+09:00">If I could get to see this man and spend some time with him</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:28:27.968+09:00">then dying after that I would have no regrets."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:28:31.215+09:00">Li Si said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:31:44.327+09:00">"These are books written by Han Fei."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:32:30.427+09:00">As a result became more eager to attack Han.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:33:11.082+09:00">To start with, the King of Han had no use for Fei.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:34:46.822+09:00">It was when the situation was desperate</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:35:11.056+09:00">that he dispatched Fei on a mission to Qin.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:35:35.002+09:00">The King of Qin was pleased enough with him</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:36:18.819+09:00">but did not quite trust him with employment.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:39:47.513+09:00">Li Si and Yao Jia sought to damage Han Fei,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:39:55.658+09:00">and they slandered him, saying,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:40:10.061+09:00">"Han Fei</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:40:31.348+09:00">is an ordinary prince from Han.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:41:46.401+09:00">At this point as your majesty is wanting to unite the feudal lords</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:42:06.577+09:00">Fei is working for Han and he is not working for Qin:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:46:21.797+09:00">this is natural enough!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:47:31.824+09:00">But if now your majesty, having kept him here without employing him</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T21:47:49.943+09:00">you send him back</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:00:19.882+09:00">this is asking for trouble for yourself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:04:32.088+09:00">It will be best to execute him for transgression of the law."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:05:03.128+09:00">The King of Qin thought this was fair enough</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:06:03.47+09:00">and he gave orders to a legal officers to deal with Fei.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:06:30+09:00">Li Si ordered someone to send Fei poison</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:06:51.686+09:00">and he got him to kill himself.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:07:11.016+09:00">Han Fei wanted to put forward his case,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:07:22.715+09:00">but he was not given an audience.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:08:04.116+09:00">The King of Qin regretted what he had done</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:08:30.299+09:00">and he sent out a man to pardon Han Fei,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_063-25a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-03-14T22:08:49.857+09:00">but by that time Fei was already dead.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
